"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45823","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-07","<p /> <p /> <p>The Department's guideline volumetric assumptions provided to bidders anticipated that the number of consultations expected as a percentage of new claim referrals would be 75 per cent. These assumptions were the Department's best estimates at the time, in the early stages of programme development. All assumptions were stated to bidders to be indicative only.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45823/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45823/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45823/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-28","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 12 March 2014, Official Report, column 255W, on Personal Independence Payment, what his Department's original guideline assumptions were of the percentage of personal independence payment new claim referrals that would involve a consultation assessment; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","194283"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45824","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-03","<p /> <p /> <p>Personal Independence Payment (PIP) is a new benefit and processes are currently bedding in. There are no time limits or targets on processing times to claims for PIP.</p><p> </p><p>We recognise the new processes are taking longer than expected and we are taking robust action to improve these, including working closely with the providers to ensure performance expectations.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45824/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45824/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45824/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-28","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 13 March 2014, Official Report, column 318W, on Personal Independence Payment, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of personal independence payment claim processing times.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","194293"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45825","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-03","<p /> <p /> <p>Officials meet regularly with both assessment providers to discuss performance. We are closely monitoring their progress against the Department's expectations for service delivery, including claim processing times and are taking robust action to drive up performance where this does not meet the required standards.</p><p> </p><p>Whilst, in line with other benefits, there are no statutory time limits on processing claims for PIP, we are working closely with our service providers to minimise the length of time claimants have to wait for assessments.We are also seeking to ensure that all the steps in the process run as smoothly as possible and that there are no barriers in our processes and systems that contribute to claims taking longer than necessary to progress</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45825/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45825/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45825/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-28","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 13 March 2014, Official Report, column 318W, on Personal Independence Payment, what discussions he has had with providers about personal independence payment claim processing times.","false","Biography information for Paul Blomfield","Sheffield Central","Paul Blomfield","194292"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45826","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-07","<p /> <p /> <p>The information you require is not available.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-04-07T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45826/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45826/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45826/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-28","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 25 March 2014, Official Report, columns 232-3W, on social security benefits: young people, if he will publish information relevant to the original question in whatever format that is available.","false","Biography information for John Healey","Wentworth and Dearne","John Healey","194288"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45827","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-02","<p>Statistics on the number of claimants who have returned to Jobcentre Plus after 104 weeks on the Work Programme by age group can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistics-tabulation-tool" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/collections/dwp-statistics-tabulation-tool</a></p><p> </p><p>Guidance for users is available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/dwp-tabulation-tool-guidance</a></p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45827/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45827/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45827/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-28","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people returning to Jobcentre Plus after two years on the Work Programme are aged under 25 years.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","194315"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45828","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-02","<p /> <p /> <p>We estimate ongoing yearly total savings of £1.92m from 14/15.</p><p> </p><p>Savings will be reinvested in providing extra digital equipment to support the delivery of an assisted service for vulnerable claimants.</p><p> </p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45828/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45828/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45828/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-28","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what estimate has been made of how much his Department is likely to save annually as a result of the removal of warm phones from Jobcentre Plus offices.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","194317"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45829","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-02","<p> </p><p> </p><p>It is not our policy to refer people to third-sector providers to use the telephone or get help in filling in our forms. As such we do not collect this information. Where third party providers are the most suitable people to provide suport or advice we would signpost claimants to them.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45829/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45829/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45829/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-28","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, whether his Department records the number of referrals made to local third-sector advice providers (a) to use the telephone, (b) for help filling in forms and (c) providing other support.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","194318"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45830","Ministry of Justice","false","2014-04-10","<p> </p><p> </p><p>Youth Offending Teams (YOTs) can request access to special needs statements from the education services arm of local authorities who hold them, but they have no access to these as of right. Under the Education (Special Educational Needs) (England) (Consolidation) Regulations 2001, local authority education services are not permitted to share these statements, without the student's consent, with external parties including YOTs, except for prescribed reasons which include where the local authority in question judges it necessary to do so in the interests of the child, on the order of a court or for the purpose of any criminal proceedings.</p><p> </p><p>Under the Children and Families Act 2014, YOTs and local authorities will be required to co-operate in the exercise of the authority's functions relating to children and young people with special educational needs, for example in the assessment for and preparation of Education and Health Care plans in relation to young people known to the YOT.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Faulks",,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45830/answer","Biography information for Lord Faulks","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45830/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45830/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2014-03-28","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government whether youth offending teams are given access to students' special needs statements as of right.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL6434"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45831","The Lord Chairman of Committees","false","2014-04-08","<p>The Encaustic Tile Programme is a seven year conservation programme to replace and repair the encaustic tiles throughout the Palace of Westminster. As part of the programme, tiles which are in good condition are either left in place or re-used elsewhere whenever possible.</p><p>In some cases, the tiles cannot be re-used elsewhere, and the Administration and Works Committee in the Lords and the Administration Committee in the Commons have agreed that, in these cases, some tiles should be kept for archival purposes, some tiles should be donated to museums or related institutions, and a limited number of tiles should be sold.</p><p>The Committees in both Houses are currently discussing the details of this proposal.</p><p> </p>",,"Lord Sewel",,"2014-04-08T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45831/answer","Biography information for Lord Sewel","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45831/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45831/answer",,,,,"200",,"Chairman of Committees (HoL)","2014-03-28","2","House of Lords","To ask the Chairman of Committees whether there are plans to sell or give away the tiles currently being replaced in the Palace of Westminster.","false","Biography information for Lord Storey",,"Lord Storey","HL6435"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45834","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","false","2014-04-10","<p>The Government is having regular discussions about the current peace talks with the Palestinian Authority and the Government of Israel. The Secretary of State for Foreign and Commonwealth Affairs, my right hon. Friend the Member for Richmond (Yorks) (Mr Hague), most recently had a discussion on 3 April with Palestinian President Mahmoud Abbas about the peace process. The Foreign Secretary met with the Israeli Minister for Intelligence, International Relations and Strategic Affairs, Yuval Steinitz on 8 April where they discussed the latest in the peace process.</p>",,"Baroness Warsi",,"2014-04-10T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45834/answer","Biography information for Baroness Warsi","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45834/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45834/answer",,,,,"16","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","Foreign and Commonwealth Office","2014-03-28","2","House of Lords","To ask Her Majesty's Government what discussions they are having with Mahmoud Abbas on continuing the negotiations with Israel for a two-state solution.","false","Biography information for Lord Turnberg",,"Lord Turnberg","HL6438"
