"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45172","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-31","<p /> <p /> <p>As announced in the Budget 2014, the maximum amount of additional State Pension that individuals can obtain under the State Pension top-up scheme (Class 3A) will be £25 per week. We intend to make details available shortly of the contribution rates by age for each £1 per week of additional pension.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45172/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45172/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45172/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what the upper limit will be of the amount of state pension top-up people can buy.","false","Biography information for Gregg McClymont","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Gregg McClymont","193915"
