"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45356","Scotland Office","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>A breakdown of the relevant data requested can be found below. No staff work term-time or are on a homeworking contract. All staff have the opportunity to work flexible working hours.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Grade</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Gender</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Reduced or Part Time hours</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Compressed Hours</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Job Share</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SCS</p></td><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Grade 6/7</p></td><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>3.3%</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>SEO</p></td><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>3.3%</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>1.7%</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>HEO</p></td><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>1.7%</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>EO</p></td><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Admin.</p></td><td><p>Male</p></td><td><p>1.7%</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>Female</p></td><td><p>1.7%</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45356/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45356/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45356/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what proportion of employees in his Department of what (a) Civil Service pay grade and (b) gender work (i) reduced hours, (ii) flexi-time, (iii) from home, (iv) a compressed working week, (v) job share, (vi) term-time only and (vii) part-time.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","193972"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45357","Scotland Office","false","2014-04-09","<p> </p><p>Neither my Rt hon Friend the Secretary of State nor I have met with the Scottish Government to discuss the introduction of a Right to Move scheme for social tenants. Under the terms of devolution responsibility for housing, and that of social housing is the responsibility of Scottish Government Ministers. <em>HomeSwap</em> Direct however, does operate across the United Kingdom for those tenants wishing to mutually exchange within the social housing sphere.</p><p> </p>","Dumfriesshire, Clydesdale and Tweeddale","David Mundell",,"2014-04-09T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45357/answer","Biography information for David Mundell","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45357/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45357/answer",,,,,"2","Scotland","Scotland","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Scotland, what discussions the Government has had with the Scottish Government on the introduction of a Right to Move scheme for social tenants.","false","Biography information for Cathy Jamieson","Kilmarnock and Loudoun","Cathy Jamieson","193789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45358","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission informs me that it does not have any current plans to carry out research to make such an assessment.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45358/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45358/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45358/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2014, Official Report, columns 622-3W, on the Electoral Register: fraud, if the Electoral Commission will make an assessment of (a) the effect of the views of politicians and (b) statements by the Electoral Commission on public perception of electoral registration.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","193832"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45359","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission informs me that it will undertake analysis of the impact of the transition to IER for all local authorities, which will include all university towns and cities, throughout the transition period. This will include publishing data by local authority, and in some cases by electoral ward, at several points during the transition period.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45359/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45359/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45359/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, pursuant to the Answer of 29 November 2013, Official Report, columns 455-6W, on the Electoral Register, for what reasons the electoral commission has no plans to undertake a direct assessment of registration rates in specific university towns and cities.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","193834"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45360","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission informs me that it regularly monitors comparative international research on electoral matters. Comparing the UK with other countries around the world, Gallup polls place the UK in the top third of countries in terms of confidence in the honesty of the electoral process.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The most recently available Gallup data from 2007-08, showed that 40% of UK respondents said they did not have confidence in the honesty of elections in the UK. This was slightly lower than the findings from Germany (44%) and Italy (43%), but significantly higher than those from Denmark (5%), Finland (8%) and Sweden (8%).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Full findings are at the following link:</p><p> </p><p><a href="http://www.gallup.com/poll/111691/Worldwide-Views-Diverge-About-Honesty-Elections.aspx" target="_blank">http://www.gallup.com/poll/111691/Worldwide-Views-Diverge-About-Honesty-Elections.aspx</a></p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45360/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45360/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45360/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, pursuant to the Answer of 29 January 2014, Official Report, columns 622-3W, on the Electoral Register: fraud, what comparative assessment he has made of the level of concern about electoral fraud in the UK and other EU countries.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","193833"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45361","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>The Electoral Commission informs me that its Report, titled ‘Readiness for the transition to Individual Electoral Registration' was published on 31 March with a copy placed in the House Library. The Commission's report includes the conclusions of its assessment of all Electoral Registration Officers' (EROs') public engagement strategies, which found that all EROs have the right plans in place to identify the challenges for their particular local area and what mechanisms they will use to engage with residents to maximise registration. The Commission has also written to the honourable member with a copy of its report.</p><p> </p>","South West Devon","Mr Gary Streeter",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45361/answer","Biography information for Sir Gary Streeter","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45361/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45361/answer",,,,,"36","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the hon. Member for South West Devon, representing the Speaker's Committee on the Electoral Commission, pursuant to the Answer of 29 November 2013, Official Report, columns 455-6W, on the Electoral Register, if he will place in the Library a copy of the Electoral Commission's review of public engagement strategies.","false","Biography information for Chris Ruane","Vale of Clwyd","Chris Ruane","193835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45362","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The Chancellor announced in this year's Budget that funding to maintain existing air connectivity to London – first announced in the 2013 Spending Round last June – will increase from £10million to £20million per year, and would be expanded to include provision for start-up aid for new air routes from UK regional airports, including those in the devolved administrations, which handle fewer than five million passengers per year.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Department for Transport is working with the Treasury to develop guidance that will clarify how the Government will ordinarily expect to interpret the European Union State aid guidelines on start-up aid for new air routes, and explain how the funding process will operate across the UK.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45362/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45362/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45362/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether the expanded Air Development Fund announced in the Budget Statement 2014 will apply throughout the UK: and how that fund will operate in the devolved jurisdictions.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","193868"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45363","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Ministers in the Department for Transport are in regular contact with the Welsh Assembly on a variety of matters; however, Ministers have not received representations from the Welsh Government or the Official Opposition regarding HS2 and Barnett consequentials.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Details of ministerial meetings with external organisations are published quarterly and can be found at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-transparency-data#meetings" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/ministerial-transparency-data#meetings</a></p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45363/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45363/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45363/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what representations he has received from the Welsh Government or the Official Opposition on Barnett consequentials for Wales resulting from future High Speed 2 expenditure.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","193879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45364","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-01","<p>The Department for Transport provides capital funding to local highway authorities, including Essex County Council, from the local highways maintenance capital block grant. Harlow falls within Essex County Council's area of responsibility and therefore we do not allocate any funds directly to the Borough Council for road maintenance.</p><p> </p><p>Since 2004 the Department has allocated the following amounts to Essex for highway maintenance:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><strong>Year</strong></td><td><p><strong>£m</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td>2004/05</td><td><p>12.626</p></td></tr><tr><td>2005/06</td><td><p>15.782</p></td></tr><tr><td>2006/07</td><td><p>16.682</p></td></tr><tr><td>2007/08</td><td><p>22.428</p></td></tr><tr><td>2008/09</td><td><p>20.706</p></td></tr><tr><td>2009/10</td><td><p>21.361</p></td></tr><tr><td>2010/11</td><td><p>20.959</p></td></tr><tr><td>2011/12</td><td><p>20.728</p></td></tr><tr><td>2012/13</td><td><p>19.838</p></td></tr><tr><td>2013/14</td><td><p>22.482*</p></td></tr><tr><td>2014/15</td><td><p>19.873*</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>* includes the top up announced in the 2012 Autumn Statement.</p><p>The Department also allocated additional funding to authorities to help repair roads damaged by various weather events and this included a further £2.116 million to Essex County Council in 2010/11 and £5.301 million in March 2011. More recently the Department for Transport has agreed to allocate over £2.7 million due to the severe wet weather the country has encountered.</p><p> </p><p>A £200 million Pothole Fund was announced in the Budget on 19 March 2014. From this, £168 million is being made available to councils in England through a bidding exercise. Further details on the fund will be made available in the coming weeks.</p><p><br>Local authorities are also able to use revenue funding allocated by the Department for Communities and Local Government through the Revenue Support Grant for maintaining their local highways. Neither capital nor revenue highways maintenance funding is ring-fenced and it is for local highway authorities to decide upon their spending priorities across the whole range of services they provide.</p><p>The Department for Transport does not centrally hold information on what proportion of this funding is spent by Essex County Council on repairing potholes.</p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45364/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45364/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45364/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how much money has been spent on repairing potholes in (a) Harlow and (b) Essex since 2004.","false","Biography information for Robert Halfon","Harlow","Robert Halfon","193871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45365","Department for Transport","false","2014-03-31","<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HS2 will provide a very significant expansion of the rail network's ability to carry passengers and freight, resulting in improvements to rail services throughout the country. It is too soon to set a final train timetable at this stage, but HS2 Ltd and Network Rail have begun a process which will allow us to identify the best possible use of the post-HS2 rail network.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>One set of assumptions, amongst many, has been developed for business case modelling purposes. These assumptions are clearly set out in <em>The Economic Case for HS2: Assumptions Report</em> published in October 2013 (<a href="http://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inserts/SA%2020_PFM%20assumptions%20report_V3_0.pdf" target="_blank">http://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inserts/SA%2020_PFM%20assumptions%20report_V3_0.pdf</a>).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","193891","2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45365/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45365/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45365/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what the proposed service pattern is for classic-compatible High Speed 2 trains serving Carlisle when (a) High Speed 2 phase 1 and (b) High Speed 2 phase 2 opens.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","193890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45366","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-01","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>The total number of employees in the department and its agencies spilt by gender is as follows:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>Female 6924</p><p> </p><p>Male 9768</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The following tables provide the information requested. Where numbers are 5 or less, we have withheld the precise number on grounds of confidentiality in line with the Data Protection Act.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45366/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45366/answer","193973 - table.doc","193973 - table.doc","Breakdown of staff information in DfT & Agencies","Breakdown of staff information in DfT & Agencies","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45366/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what proportion of employees in his Department of what (a) Civil Service pay grade and (b) gender work (i) reduced hours, (ii) flexi-time, (iii) from home, (iv) a compressed working week, (v) job share, (vi) term-time only and (vii) part-time.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","193973"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45367","Department for Transport","false","2014-03-31","<p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>HS2 will provide a very significant expansion of the rail network's ability to carry passengers and freight, resulting in improvements to rail services throughout the country. It is too soon to set a final train timetable at this stage, but HS2 Ltd and Network Rail have begun a process which will allow us to identify the best possible use of the post-HS2 rail network.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>One set of assumptions, amongst many, has been developed for business case modelling purposes. These assumptions are clearly set out in <em>The Economic Case for HS2: Assumptions Report</em> published in October 2013 (<a href="http://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inserts/SA%2020_PFM%20assumptions%20report_V3_0.pdf" target="_blank">http://assets.hs2.org.uk/sites/default/files/inserts/SA%2020_PFM%20assumptions%20report_V3_0.pdf</a>).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill","193890","2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45367/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45367/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45367/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what plans he has for Penrith North Lakes, Oxenholme Lake District and Lancaster to be served by classic-compatible High Speed 2 trains.","false","Biography information for Mr Jamie Reed","Copeland","Mr Jamie Reed","193891"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45368","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>My officials will collate the key correspondence sent in the last five years between Ministers in Welsh and UK Government on electrification of the mainline between Swansea and London and deposit this in the Libraries of the House.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45368/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45368/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45368/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will publish and place in the Library all correspondence sent in the last five years between the Welsh and UK Governments on electrification of the mainline between Swansea and London.","false","Biography information for Jonathan Edwards","Carmarthen East and Dinefwr","Jonathan Edwards","193785"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45369","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-01","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>Department for Transport officials are working with those in Northern Ireland to support any Driver and Vehicle Agency (DVA) staff who might need to learn new skills to secure alternative employment. An initial meeting has taken place to discuss the details. Officials will continue to work together to ensure appropriate support is given to staff at the DVA during the transition period.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p>","Wimbledon","Stephen Hammond",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45369/answer","Biography information for Stephen Hammond","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45369/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45369/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, if he will take steps to ensure people who are currently employed by the Driver and Vehicle Agency receive training to enable them to take up local posts in other Government departments and public bodies..","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","193762"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45370","Department for Transport","false","2014-03-31","<p> </p><p>The safety of young people on our roads is very important to us. Too many young people die, too often; we are wrestling with how to make things safer, while not unduly restricting the freedom of our young people. We want young people to be able to get to work and training, to education and to leisure activities, and we want them to do so safely. We are finding this a difficult balance, with passionate voices on both sides.</p><p> </p><p><br> On 27 January 2014, we held a meeting with the insurance industry and agreed the Department would commission new research into how telematics can change the behaviour and attitudes of learner drivers. We look forward to insurance companies sharing their data so that we can undertake this research. <br> <br> We are also in the process of undertaking some focus groups with parents, young people and employers to get a better understanding of the issues from their perspective.</p><p> </p><p><br> <br></p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45370/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45370/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45370/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when he plans to announce the findings of the Green Paper on improving the safety and reducing risks to young drivers.","false","Biography information for Andrea Leadsom","South Northamptonshire","Andrea Leadsom","193736"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45371","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>As part of its Aiming for Zero safety programme, the Highways Agency established a Road Worker Safety programme designed to reduce risk exposure to road workers, a particular focus of which is to reduce the incidences of carriageway crossing by road workers. Within this programme, a number of projects have been commissioned to test simplifications and other changes to temporary traffic management arrangements to reduce road worker exposure to live traffic whilst maintaining standards of safety for road users. Some of these projects have been completed already; for example Signs Simplification, implemented December 2011, and Offside Signs Removal techniques, implemented November 2012.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The introduction of these innovative changes has already enabled a very substantial reduction in the number of carriageway crossings, leading to a proportionate reduction in road worker risk exposure. In March 2014 the Highways Agency published further guidance on the Offside Signs Removal technique, allowing it to be used to close a four lane carriageway. The Highways Agency is continuing to work with its supply chain to take forward further projects within this programme with the aim of further reducing road worker risk.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45371/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45371/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45371/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what steps his Department and the Highways Agency are taking to reduce the risk of death or serious injury to road workers on the motorway network.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","193978"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45372","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p><strong> </strong></p><p> </p><p>There are no products used by the Highways Agency which have been mandated in terms of what is used for road traffic management. These products are used by staff and contractors for the Highways Agency and such items are procured using a specification via a tender arrangement and not directed by the Department for Transport, or Ministers.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45372/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45372/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45372/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what commercial products his Department or the Highways Agency has mandated for use in road traffic management on the motorway network in the last 10 years.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","193979"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45373","Department for Transport","false","2014-04-03","<p> </p><p>The Highways Agency has made the following progress in supporting the Department in delivering Government Small and Medium Enterprises (SME) procurement policy:</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>made the use of Project Bank Account a default position on all contracts awarded since October 2011. This considerably speeds up payment times to the supply chain, including any SMEs. Highways Agency contracted business now accounts for over 80% of the overall government target for directing spend through project bank accounts,</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>increased visibility of SME supply chain spend through contracts using a combination of strengthened contract reporting requirements, project bank account data and supply chain survey. It is now the case that over 30% of supply chain spend on HA contracts is with SMEs, and in some cases this can be as high as 50% of overall spend. The SME spend through the Agency's planned collaborative delivery framework, currently being tendered, is expected to range between 30-50% of overall spend,</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>attended and presented at ‘Meet the Buyer' events around the country, with the two most recent of these being in Sheffield and Reading in late 2013. The opportunity was taken further to reduce barriers for SMEs by helping them identify sources of information on potential direct opportunities (HA website, Contracts Finder, Tenders Electronic Daily (TED)), plus providing attendees with advice on how to seek extended supply chain opportunities in relation to larger contracts,</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>launched a new page on their website targeting and providing information for SMEs, linked here- <a title="http://www.highways.gov.uk/about-us/procurement/supplier-selection-and-development/small-medium-entrprises-smes" href="http://www.highways.gov.uk/about-us/procurement/supplier-selection-and-development/small-medium-entrprises-smes" target="_blank">http://www.highways.gov.uk/about-us/procurement/supplier-selection-and-development/small-medium-entrprises-smes</a>,</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>increased use of Open procedure through the procurement process, with the Agency now looking, where feasible, to breakdown lot structures in framework agreements to increase attractiveness to a broader and deeper supply chain,</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>amended its Instruction for Tenderers (IFT) in 2013 to state that “The Highways Agency is committed to removing barriers to SME participation in its contracts and this includes sub-contracting opportunities. If you are proposing to sub-contract part of this contract, you should provide assurance that you have considered how SMEs could play a part and details of the measures you have put in place to encourage and enable their participation as your sub-contractors. If you are awarded the contract, we will ask you to provide regular information about your spend with SMEs under the contract and may publicise good practice on our websites and report such expenditure to other Government Departments'', and</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><ul><li>become an active member of a cross government Cabinet Office led SME Champions Group looking at strategic alignment, sharing best practice and promoting behavioural change towards SMEs</li></ul><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>The Highways Agency awarded a Temporary Traffic Management framework (TTM) in March 2013 (estimated value £660 million over 4 years). Breaking down the lot structure for this encouraged application/interest from SME suppliers, resulting in one of the eight successful suppliers being an SME (Forest Traffic Services Ltd).</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>More broadly, since January 2010, 93 SME companies, names of which appear below, have been awarded HA contracts and/or task orders via frameworks, for the procurement of a range of goods, services and works with a total award value of just over £193m.</p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p>","Scarborough and Whitby","Mr Robert Goodwill",,"2014-04-03T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45373/answer","Biography information for Mr Robert Goodwill","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45373/answer","193980 - table.docx","193980 - table.docx","SME companies awarded HA contracts ","SME companies awarded HA contracts ","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45373/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department and the Highways Agency have made in delivering the Government's small and medium-sized enterprise procurement policy in road traffic management on the motorway network since 2010; what goods and services have been procured from which companies; at what cost; and what processes were used for the procurement of those goods and services.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","193980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45374","Wales Office","false","2014-04-02","<p> </p><p>The proportion of staff in the Wales Office working flexibly is set out the enclosed table.</p><p><br></p>","Preseli Pembrokeshire","Stephen Crabb",,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45374/answer","Biography information for Stephen Crabb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45374/answer","PQ 193975 - Table.doc","PQ 193975 - Table.doc","PQ 193975 - Table: Wales Office Working Patterns","PQ 193975 - Table: Wales Office Working Patterns","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45374/answer",,,,,"28","Wales","Wales","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Wales, what proportion of employees in his Department of what (a) Civil Service pay grade and (b) gender work (i) reduced hours, (ii) flexi-time, (iii) from home, (iv) a compressed working week, (v) job share, (vi) term-time only and (vii) part-time.","false","Biography information for Lucy Powell","Manchester Central","Lucy Powell","193975"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45376","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-02","<p /> <p /> <p>This information is not held centrally to the level of detail required to distinguish the traffic management sector from others in the construction industry. It would incur disproportinate cost to find this information.</p><p> </p><p>The Health and Safety Executive (HSE) works with the industry to help develop traffic management layouts or schemes which improve the safety of those working on high speed roads. It also carries out investigations of incidents and complaints and takes enforcement action in line with its published emforcement policy.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45376/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45376/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45376/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what steps the Health and Safety Executive has taken to enforce the Health and Safety at Work Act 1974 in respect of employees in the traffic management industry in the last 10 years for which information is available.","false","Biography information for Lord McCrea of Magherafelt and Cookstown","South Antrim","Dr William McCrea","193976"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45377","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-01","<p /> <p /> <p>The Pensions Advisory Service provides information and guidance over multiple distribution channels including by telephone, web chat, online and written enquiries and face to face via outreach activity. The outreach activity includes shows, forums and similar events. All guidance is tailored to the individuals' personal circumstances.</p><p> </p><p>The data for the last five years are set out in the table below:</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p>Year</p></td><td><p>2009/2010</p></td><td><p>2010/2011</p></td><td><p>2011/2012</p></td><td><p>2012/2013</p></td><td><p>2013/2014</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Helpline customers</p><p>Includes calls, online enquiries, webchats and 1<sup>st</sup> party complaints</p></td><td><p>99,663</p></td><td><p>87,712</p></td><td><p>93,505</p></td><td><p>84,228</p></td><td><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p> </p><p>76,348 (as at 28th February)</p><p> </p><p> </p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Outreach work</p></td><td><p>6,457 people spoken to at TPAS events/presentations</p></td><td><p>7,577</p></td><td><p>3,786</p></td><td><p>1,091</p></td><td><p>1,400 estimate to date</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p> </p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45377/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45377/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45377/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people received face to face guidance from the Pension Advisory Service in each of the last five years.","false","Biography information for Gregg McClymont","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Gregg McClymont","193944"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45379","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-01","<p /> <p /> <p /> <p /> <p>The investment strategy for the National Employment Savings Trust (NEST) is the responsibility of the NEST Trustees who will consider, if in the best interests of their members, there needs to be any change in NEST's investment approach.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45379/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45379/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45379/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the planned changes to pensions on the investment strategy of the National Employment Savings Trust.","false","Biography information for Gregg McClymont","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Gregg McClymont","193950"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45386","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-01","<p /> <p /> <p>The Budget announced that from April 2015, the tax rules for how people access their defined contribution pension savings will be simplified to allow individuals aged 55 or over to withdraw their savings however they wish, subject to their marginal rate of income tax.</p><p> </p><p>Allowing individuals to exercise greater choice over how they access their retirement savings may mean that some people who would have previously chosen to opt out may no longer do so. This is more likely to have an effect on the choices of older workers.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45386/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45386/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45386/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the planned changes to pensions on opt-out rates of auto enrolment.","false","Biography information for Gregg McClymont","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Gregg McClymont","193948"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45388","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-01","<p /> <p /> <p>The information requested is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><p>Outcomes of functional assessments by prognosis of 2 years or more for the ESA work-related activity group, Great Britain: October 2008 – September 2013</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>WRAG: Claimants with a prognosis of 2 years or more</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>New Claims - Initial assessment</p></td><td><p>11,800</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>New Claims – Repeat assessment</p></td><td><p>19,700</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Incapacity Benefit Reassessments</p></td><td><p>73,100</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: Data in the tables above is derived from administrative data held by the DWP and assessment data provided by Atos Healthcare.</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>1. Figures are rounded to the nearest 100.</p><p>2. The outcome recorded is the final DWP Decision Maker's decision or the recommendation made by the Atos Healthcare Professional where the Decision Maker's decision is not yet available.</p><p>3. The data presented above comes from benefit claims data held by the Department for Work and Pensions. It related to new and repeat ESA claims and Incapacity Benefit (IB) claims reassessments. In October 2008, ESA replaced IB for new claims. Starting with a trial in October 2010, and reaching a full scale national roll-out in April 2011, existing IB claims began to be phased out, with claimants reassessed to see if they qualify for ESA instead.</p><p>The reassessment of existing incapacity benefits claimants started in October 2010 with a trial in the Burnley and Aberdeen areas. These are included in the table.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45388/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45388/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45388/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45388/answer/previousversion/3955","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people who have been given a prognosis that engagement in work is unlikely in the longer term have been placed in the work-related activity group for employment and support allowance since October 2008.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","193893"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45390","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-31","<p /> <p>The Work Programme is designed to be flexible and tailored to each individual, with some participants requiring more support than others which may include assistance in improving their literacy and numeracy skills. The Department has a robust performance management regime which includes assurance of service delivery at individual participant level</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45390/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45390/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45390/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what measures he has in place to establish the extent to which work programme providers have assisted participants to improve their literacy and numeracy skills.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","193894"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45392","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-31","<p /> <p /> <p>Estimates were made of both the future AME expenditure and the revenue from contributions in 2015-16 and 2016-17 which would determine future state pension expenditure levels. Estimates made by the Department were certified by the Office for Budget Responsibility. Figures for the medium term impacts in cash terms were published on page 46 in Budget 2014: policy costings available at:</p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/295067/PU1638_policy_costings_bud_2014_with_correction_slip.pdf" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/uploads/system/uploads/attachment_data/file/295067/PU1638_policy_costings_bud_2014_with_correction_slip.pdf</a> .</p><p> </p><p>Further information on the long-term Exchequer impact in 2013-14 price terms is included in the table below. As noted in the policy costings document, there is uncertainty about levels of take-up of this policy. If take-up was higher than assumed both AME and Revenue would increase and if take-up was lower than assumed then both would decrease.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>AME</p></td><td><p>Revenue</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2014-15</p></td><td><p>0</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2015-16</p></td><td><p>-15</p></td><td><p>+415</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2016-17</p></td><td><p>-50</p></td><td><p>+410</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2017-18</p></td><td><p>-65</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2018-19</p></td><td><p>-65</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2019-20</p></td><td><p>-60</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2020-21</p></td><td><p>-60</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2021-22</p></td><td><p>-55</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2022-23</p></td><td><p>-55</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2023-24</p></td><td><p>-55</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2024-25</p></td><td><p>-50</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2025-26</p></td><td><p>-45</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2026-27</p></td><td><p>-45</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2027-28</p></td><td><p>-40</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2028-29</p></td><td><p>-40</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2029-30</p></td><td><p>-35</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2030-31</p></td><td><p>-35</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2031-32</p></td><td><p>-30</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2032-33</p></td><td><p>-30</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>2033-34</p></td><td><p>-25</p></td><td><p>0</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Notes to table: Figures are in £m, 2013-14 price terms, rounded to nearest £5m.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb","193916","2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45392/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45392/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45392/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he made of the effect of the option for people to top up their state pension on state pensions expenditure.","false","Biography information for Gregg McClymont","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Gregg McClymont","193926"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45393","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-01","<p /> <p /> <p>The information requested is shown in the table below:</p><p> </p><p>Outcomes of functional assessments by prognosis of 2 years or more for the ESA work-related activity group, Great Britain: October 2008 – September 2013</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p> </p></td><td><p>WRAG: Claimants with a prognosis of 2 years or more</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>New Claims - Initial assessment</p></td><td><p>11,800</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>New Claims – Repeat assessment</p></td><td><p>19,700</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>Incapacity Benefit Reassessments</p></td><td><p>73,100</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p><p>Source: Data in the tables above is derived from administrative data held by the DWP and assessment data provided by Atos Healthcare.</p><p> </p><p>Notes:</p><p>1. Figures are rounded to the nearest 100.</p><p>2. The outcome recorded is the final DWP Decision Maker's decision or the recommendation made by the Atos Healthcare Professional where the Decision Maker's decision is not yet available.</p><p>3. The data presented above comes from benefit claims data held by the Department for Work and Pensions. It related to new and repeat ESA claims and Incapacity Benefit (IB) claims reassessments. In October 2008, ESA replaced IB for new claims. Starting with a trial in October 2010, and reaching a full scale national roll-out in April 2011, existing IB claims began to be phased out, with claimants reassessed to see if they qualify for ESA instead.</p><p>The reassessment of existing incapacity benefits claimants started in October 2010 with a trial in the Burnley and Aberdeen areas. These are included in the table.</p>","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning",,"2014-04-01T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45393/answer","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45393/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45393/answer","Hemel Hempstead","Mike Penning","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45393/answer/previousversion/3956","Biography information for Sir Mike Penning","29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many people on incapacity benefit who have been given a prognosis that engagement in work is unlikely in the longer term have been placed in the work-related activity group since October 2010.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","193896"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45402","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-04-02","<p /> <p /> <p>The government believes people should be trusted to make their own choices about how to use their savings to fund their retirement. These measures fundamentally change the way that people can access their retirement savings, and therefore people are free to vary the mix of income and capital they hold in retirement.</p><p> </p><p>Alongside these changes, the government is taking measures to ensure everyone approaching retirement is aware of the choices they have. Pension providers and schemes will be required, by April 2015, to offer all individuals retiring with a defined contribution pension pot free and impartial face-to-face guidance on their retirement choices.</p>","Thornbury and Yate","Steve Webb",,"2014-04-02T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45402/answer","Biography information for Steve Webb","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45402/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45402/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of the effect of the planned changes to pensions on retirement incomes from private and workplace pensions.","false","Biography information for Gregg McClymont","Cumbernauld, Kilsyth and Kirkintilloch East","Gregg McClymont","193939"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45405","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2014-03-31","<p /> <p /> <p>Legislation prevents 18 year olds who claim JSA claiming Child Benefit (if eligible) and vice versa. 18 year olds claiming JSA can benefit from a traineeship, we are working to ensure that all young people who could benefit from a traineeship are able to do so.</p>","Wirral West","Esther McVey",,"2014-03-31T12:00:00.00Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45405/answer","Biography information for Esther McVey","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45405/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/45405/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2014-03-26","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment he has made of whether the unavailability of child benefit for 18 year olds in receipt of jobseeker's allowance is discouraging the take-up of traineeships.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","193897"
